Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: Selenium driver not found

# Reinstall geckodriver
sudo apt remove firefox-geckodriver
sudo apt install firefox-geckodriver -y
Issue: Rate limiting / blocked requests

Add longer delays between requests (10-15 seconds)
Rotate User-Agent headers
Use proxy servers for distributed requests
Respect robots.txt and terms of service
Issue: BeautifulSoup parsing errors

Verify HTML structure hasn't changed (websites update frequently)
Add error handling with try-except blocks
Print response.text to debug parsing issues
Use browser developer tools to inspect current HTML structure
Issue: Image upload failures

Verify image file exists and is readable
Check file size (some platforms have limits)
Ensure image format is supported
Convert images to JPEG if needed: convert input.png output.jpg
